<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="541" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,716,958]" pageId="2" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,716,742]" pageId="2" pageNumber="541">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Notogastral surface never smooth, either with papilli, tubercles or polygonal sculptures. Pygidial setae branched, tree shaped or ciliate, presence of strong pygidial neotrichy (&gt;18 pairs).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1293,788,815]" pageId="2" pageNumber="541" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,716,958]" box="[199,1293,788,815]" pageId="2" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,300,789,815]" pageId="2" pageNumber="541">Ecology.</emphasis>
Natural habitats include litter and soil ecosystems, also found in moss and on epiphytes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="541" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,716,958]" pageId="2" pageNumber="541">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,824,850]" pageId="2" pageNumber="541">Distribution</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[359,428,824,851]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[152,255,1925,1949]" captionTargetBox="[155,1431,985,1897]" captionTargetId="figure-195@2.[151,1436,982,1901]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution map of the genus Papillacarus (Vepracarus) Aoki, 1965." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4570513" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4570513/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="541">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
